    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Based on the design doc https://hackmd.io/soUUA3-dTYCSeBx4bkRc-Q#Migration\r\nwe have decided to pick option 2, which is \r\n\r\nTake a DB snapshot/backup before turning on the feature flag. if the DB gets corrupted, the user has to restore the DB from backup.\r\n\r\n**Pro:**\r\n- Simple\r\n- No code changes required\r\n**Con:**\r\n- Node should start syncing from the restored point\r\n- Extra space for backup\r\n\r\nThis has to be added to the release doc to make the user realise the risk he is taking.\r\n",
